Canada Employment Insurance Recipients Fall 7 Straight Months

-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 
2011-06-23T12:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/canada-employment-insurance-recipients-fall-7-straight-months.html
The number of Canadians receiving
jobless benefits posted a seventh consecutive monthly decline in
April,  Statistics Canada  said.  The number of regular beneficiaries declined 1.1 percent to
598,370 on a seasonally adjusted basis.  From the year-ago month, the total number of recipients
fell 11.3 percent, the Ottawa-based agency said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
